Field Detail

adsBias

protected float adsBias
Bias for ads: if filter matches a url to an ad (for HTMLPages or MediaElements), multiply bias by this number. Special values: 0 reject ads (eg, filter matches), altogether

count

protected int count
The number of loops through the web crawler. A performance statistic that roughly corresponds to how many new Containers have been queued for download and parse, during this session.

rejectDomains

protected ecologylab.generic.HashMapWriteSynch<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> rejectDomains
Hashtable of domains the information space author doesn't want any information elements from.

badSeeds

protected int badSeeds
A count of seeds whose downloading failed. Used during startup, to determine whether it is time to start the crawler. We make sure to download all seeds before giving resources to the crawler. This makes startup fairer; otherwise, the first recorded seeds get too much priority.

seeds

protected java.util.Vector seeds
Set of expected seed download Containers).

LO_PRIORITY

protected static final int LO_PRIORITY
Priority to run at when we seem to have an overabundance of MediaElements ready for display.

protected static final int PRIORITY

Constant Field Values

downloadLinksAutomatically

protected ecologylab.appframework.types.prefs.PrefBoolean downloadLinksAutomatically
Controls whether or not we periodically automatically download the Containers associated with hrefs that have been discovered. In other words, controls whether or not we crawl at all. Set as a preference at runtime, and via a menu entry.

thread

protected java.lang.Thread thread
The web crawler thread.

traversablePrefixes

protected ecologylab.collections.PrefixCollection traversablePrefixes
Address prefixes derived from original seeding, traversable| seeding specs, and server-side redirects. Defines the spanning set of basis vectors of the information space, when limit traversal (stay close) is true.

untraversablePrefixes

protected ecologylab.collections.PrefixCollection untraversablePrefixes
Untraversable urls defined at seeding time. These supercede traversable specs.

crawlerDownloadMonitor

protected static final ecologylab.concurrent.DownloadMonitor crawlerDownloadMonitor
This DownloadMonitor is used by the web crawler (i.e., ContentIntegrator.run()). It sometimes gets paused by GoogleSearch to promote downloading of search results.

dndDownloadMonitor

protected static final ecologylab.concurrent.DownloadMonitor dndDownloadMonitor
This is the DownloadMonitor used by to process drag and drop operations. It gets especially high priority, in order to provide rapid response to the user.

seedingDownloadMonitor

traversable

public void traversable(ecologylab.net.ParsedURL purl)
Add the directory that this URL references to the traversable set; that is, to the bounding set of path prefixes that we are willing to download from, given "limit traversal." This is called automatically, as well as through traversable|; thus it parses to the directory level, removing any filename portion of the URL.
